Package com.msasc.lib.fx

Class Buttons

java.lang.Object
com.msasc.lib.fx.Buttons
public class Buttons extends Object
Button utilities. Buttons all around this development system are expected to have properties set in the user data, properties like the button group, the order in the group, or any useful property to handle the action.
Author:
Miquel Sas

    • button

      public static javafx.scene.control.Button button(String id, String text, boolean defaultButton, boolean cancelButton, boolean close)
      Return the button.
      Parameters:
      id - The button id.
      text - The text.
      defaultButton - A boolean.
      cancelButton - A boolean.
      close - A boolean to set the close property, used in windows to close it after executing the button initial action if any..
      Returns:
      The button.
